description:
Manchester City and Real Madrid are scheduled to play in the UEFA Champions League quarter-finals on April 9 and April 17, 2024.

This market will resolve to "Man City" if Manchester City advances to the semi-finals of the UEFA Champions League by winning their tie against Real Madrid. 

This market will resolve to "Madrid" if Real Madrid advances to the semi-finals of the UEFA Champions League by winning their tie against Manchester City. 

If the tie between Manchester City and Real Madrid is postponed to a date before June 1, 2024, this market's timeframe will extend to the new match dates. If the tie is canceled, or postponed to a date in June or later, this market will resolve immediately to "50-50".

This market may be resolved immediately upon the completion of the second leg of the tie.
